<HEADLINE> Qingdao Hosts International Beer Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- An international beer festival
opened today in this coastal city in east China's Shandong
Province.
</P>
<P>
Some 20,000 people, including 40 beer producers from both at
home and abroad, attended the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The festival, which has been held for six times in the city --
known for its Tsingtao brand beer, was sponsored by local
government together with the National Tourism Administration, the
Ministry of Internal Trade and the China Council for the Promotion
of International Trade.
</P>
<P>
The festival will end on July 23. 
</P>
