<HEADLINE> Good Prospects for Cyprus Stock Exchange: Finance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Exchange will
witness a better performance in the near future, as the
government intends to introduce new incentives and measures which
will strengthen investment activity, Finance Minister
Christodoulos Christodoulou said here today.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at the inauguration ceremony of the new
floor of the Cyprus Stock Exchange here.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus Stock Exchange's course and its contribution to
the Republic's economic development are satisfying, the minister
said.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that the Cyprus Stock Exchange must be upgraded
on a solid basis in order to become the stock exchange of the
region, and not only that of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus Stock Exchange was officially inaugurated in March,
1996 in a bid to upgrade Cyprus' monetary system and establish
itself as a regional exchange to serve a wider area.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the present state of the economy, Christodoulou
said that the difficulties in the first three months of the year
are decreasing, thanks to the measures taken by the government.
</P>
<P>
"The economy is already recovering, and this recovery is
expected to continue," he added.
</P>
<P>
The minister also disclosed that the 1998 state budgets will
reflect the government's development aims, as expenditure for
development and infrastructure will increase by 10 percent
compared with that of 1997, reaching 250 million Cyprus pounds
(about 500 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
