<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leaders Worldwide Congratulate China on HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Secretary of the World Federation of Trade Unions
(WFTU), Aleksandr Zharikov, in his message to Jiang, congratulated
the Chinese government and people on behalf of the 135 million
WFTU members in 127 countries across the world.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's return on July 1 marked an important step toward
China's reunification with all its territories seized by
colonialists, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hailing the event as "a victory for the universal cause of
peace and justice," Zharikov said it is also a victory for peoples
around the world, and a milestone in over 150 years of joint
struggle against imperialism and colonialism.
</P>
<P>
He hoped for a closer cooperation of his organization with the
Chinese people, including the people of Hong Kong who now become
the true master of the territory.
</P>
