<HEADLINE> Cambodia's Acting Parliament Chief Calls for Emergency Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Acting president of Cambodia's
National Assembly, Loy Sim Chheag, today asked deputies to be
prepared for an emergency parliamentary session in days.
</P>
<P>
In a speech broadcast on national television, Loy asked all
deputies in the capital Phnom Penh to contact the secretariat of
the National Assembly, or the parliament, as soon as possible so
that a session could be convened in the following days.
</P>
<P>
He psaid that tensions in Phnom Penh have eased and life in
this capital has returned to normal.
</P>
<P>
He said the coming meeting is an important one that has a
bearing on the highest interests of the Cambodian people.
</P>
<P>
He promised that immunities of the deputies will be respected.
</P>
<P>
Loy is secretary-general of the FUNCINPEC Party led by First
Prime Minister Prince Norodom Ranariddh, who was ousted by Second
Prime Minister Hun Sen.
</P>
<P>
Troops loyal to the rival prime ministers were involved in
heavy fightings in Phnom Penh from Saturday morning to Sunday
evening.
</P>
<P>
As political tension flared up, the National Assembly has been
paralyzed since April. 
</P>
