<HEADLINE> Leaders Worldwide Congratulate China on HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Leaders from around the world sent
messages of congratulation to Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
Premier Li Peng and Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen
on Hong Hong's return to China on July 1.
</P>
<P>
China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong is an important event reflecting the failure of colonism at
the end of this century, Libyan leader Muammar Ghaddafi said in
his message dated July 4.
</P>
<P>
Malta's President Ugo Mifsud Bonnici, in his message to Jiang,
said that under the concept of "one country, two systems," the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of the People's Republic
of China will keep its position as one of the world's most
successful business centers.
</P>
<P>
Residents of Hong Kong will maintain and further improve their
standards of living, civil rights and status, Bonnici said.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma said in his message Jiang,
"The return of Hong Kong to China is an epoch-making event. With
great joy, I, on behalf of the Ukrainian people and in my own
name, extend to you, and through you, to the friendly Chinese
people my congratulations."
</P>
<P>
Ukraine supports the policy taken by Chinese leaders to
safeguard their country's territorial integrity, oppose hegemonism
and resist political, economic and other means of pressure in
state-to-state relations, Kuchma said, adding that the peaceful
return of Hong Kong is the natural result of this policy.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that China will successfully resolve the questions
of Macao and Taiwan in the same way," Kuchma said.
</P>
<P>
He said, "I firmly believe that Ukraine and China will continue
their successful cooperation to elevate their bilateral relations
into a strategic partnership and that the two sides will do their
best to support each other politically in order to safeguard their
sovereignty and territorial integrity."
</P>
<P>
General Secretary of the World Federation of Trade Unions
(WFTU), Aleksandr Zharikov, in his message to Jiang, congratulated
the Chinese government and people on behalf of the 135 million
WFTU members in 127 countries across the world.
</P>
<P>
