<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Produces 26 Million Doses of Veterinary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Debre-Zeit Veterinary
Institute of Ethiopia produced 26 million doses of various
vaccinations and distributed them to customers both inside and
outside of the country during the just ended 1996/97 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The institute, about 40 kms away from Addis Ababa, was
established 33 years ago with a capacity of 4 million doses
annually.
</P>
<P>
According to director of the institute Antonio, the increase
of production last fiscal year was the result of the construction
of a new building for vaccination production center and
installation of new and modern equipment at a total cost of 2.5
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Antonio said the institute is now producing 14 types of
vaccinations.
</P>
<P>
The vaccinations are being exported to Eritrea, Angola, Yemen
and Rwanda, he said, adding that although certain middle east
countries have requested to buy vaccinations, it has not been
realized due to transportation problems.
</P>
<P>
The institute has planned to produce 56 million doses in
1997/98 fiscal year starting on July 8, 1997, according to the
director. 
</P>
</TEXT>
