<HEADLINE> Ratings Affirmed for Hongkong's Hang Seng Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- IBCA, Europe's international credit
rating agency, has affirmed the Individual rating assigned to Hang
Seng Bank of Hongkong at A/B.
</P>
<P>
The highest Individual rating awarded by IBCA is A.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the agency today also affirms the bank's
Legal rating of 3, which reflects Hang Seng's role as an important
member of the HSBC group.
</P>
<P>
Legal ratings are evaluated on the basis of the likelihood of
support for an institution from owners or government authorities
if it ran into difficulties.
</P>
<P>
According to IBCA, Hang Seng is an exceptionally profitable
bank with a highly liquid, low risk balance sheet and strong
capital ratios. Its cost to income ratio, at 25.7%, is one of the
world's lowest, and results from efficient management and a focus
in the loan book on residential mortgage loans, with high volumes
and relatively low costs.
</P>
<P>
While Hang Seng has a significant proportion of its loans
exposed to Hongkong's property market, the downturn in this market
during 1994 and 1995 did not have a significant impact on asset
quality.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng did experience an increase in bad debt levels in 1996
but its operating performance and financial condition remain
exceptionally strong by any standard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
