<HEADLINE> 9 Killed in Road Accident in Southern Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Reports from Aswan Public Hospital
indicated that eight Dutch nationals and an Egyptian were killed
when a tourist bus collided with a truck in southern Egypt today,
the Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier report, the MENA said that altogether 12 Dutch
tourists were killed in the accident that happened at the
Aswan-Abu Simbl land road, about 900 kilometers south of Cairo, at
l5:30 local time.
</P>
<P>
Other 15 people were injured and rushed to hospital for medical
treatment, said MENA. Eight of them were Dutch, two Belgian and
five Egyptian.
</P>
<P>
Nine tourists left hospital after having received the required
medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
Governor of Aswan Salah Misbah announced a state of emergency
in local hospitals while five ambulances rushed to the scene of
the accident to transport and extend first aid services to
the casualties.
</P>
<P>
Every day, thousands of foreign tourists swarmed to the
country's southern resorts that are famous for their pharaonic
relics and spectacular landscape. 
</P>
</TEXT>
