<HEADLINE> PNA Feels Urgent Need for Pan-Arab Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian leadership feels the
urgent need for holding a Pan-Arab Summit in the pinch of Israeli
arrogance, the Egyptian MENA news agency today quoted a
Palestinian official as saying.
</P>
<P>
"We feel it urgent that such a summit to be held to counter
Israel's arrogance, repeated aggression on our sanctities,
confiscation of land and freeze of the Mideast peace process,"
said Mohamed Sobieh, the Palestinian permanent delegate to the
Arab League.
</P>
<P>
Sobieh was quoted as speaking to Saudi newspaper "Al Riyad" in
an interview that such a summit is necessary "at this difficult
moment for the Arabs."
</P>
<P>
Venue and date of this summit will be set through recent
consultations, contacts and coordination among Arab leaders, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu is pushing the region
into danger, he said, noting that the Palestinian people will
continue to defend their rights and land by all means.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian-Israeli talks have been bogged down since March
by the Jewish state's construction of a new settlement in the
Arab East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The West Bank town of Hebron has been the scene of almost daily
clashes since an Israeli woman put up posters on Palestinian shops
a week ago depicting the Prophet Muhammad as a pig.
</P>
<P>
Palestinians have also accused Israeli troops and Jewish
settlers of breaking into an Arab school in Hebron and ransacking
and tearing copies of Koran.
</P>
<P>
In face of escalating clashes in the Palestinian territories,
the Cairo-based Arab League is considering the possibilities of
holding an Arab summit to discuss the deadlocked peace process.
</P>
<P>
Assistant Secretary General for Political Affairs Zakareya
Mohammed Ismail, said Sunday that the diplomatic moves and
bilateral contacts taking place among Arab leaders send a message
on the dangers of the Israeli settlement policy.
</P>
<P>
But the Arab League has not yet received any Palestinian
request to convene the summit, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
