sales, would deal "a serious blow to banditry."
</P>
<P>
Before signing these decrees Yeltsin met with First
Vice-Premier Boris Nemtsov, who regarded the fourth decree as
important as "the decree to renounce authorized banks".
</P>
<P>
The president said the decrees on production sharing
agreements and measures to cut down oil companies debts to the
state were of "international importance". 
