<HEADLINE> California Wildfire Nearly Contained </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The wildfire that has burned
more than 1,500 hectares of brush in Southern California was
expected to be totally contained late today as firefighters has
cut a line around 92 percent of the blaze, local media reports
said.
</P>
<P>
The fire, started Saturday by a man using illegal fireworks,
has burned 3,750 acres (1,560 hectares) of brush in the San
Bernardino National Forest.
</P>
<P>
As moist, overcast conditions were helping firefighters to keep
the upper hand on the fire, the U.S. Forest Service said the fire
was expected to be fully contained by 6 p.m. local time today.
</P>
<P>
The total costs of fighting the fire has reached 1.3 million
U.S. dollars so far. A helicopter pilot was killed when his
water-dropping craft crashed in a remote part of the forest
Sunday. 
</P>
