objective is to become a major meaningful economic power in the
world," he said.
</P>
<P>
There is growing cooperation between South Africa and France,
especially in the area of joint production, which should be
actively pursued in the future, Erwin said.
</P>
<P>
French Minister of Foreign Trade Jacques Dondoux, who opened
the exhibition, said the French presence in South Africa has
greatly increased since 1994, noting "France has become the
fourth most important investor in South Africa."
</P>
<P>
However, Dondoux added that France still has more work to do.
"Our companies supply under four percent of South African
imports, an inadequate percentage compared to the results
achieved by our main European partners," he said.
</P>
<P>
About 145 French companies, including Michelin, Peugeot,
Dassault and Total are represented at the exhibition. Eighty
percent of exhibitors are small and medium-sized companies.
