<HEADLINE> Ranariddh's Son Is in Singapore: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Norodom Chakravuth, son of
Cambodia's First Prime Minister Prince Norodom Ranariddh, together
with several members of his staff, arrived here today, as fighting
continued in Cambodia, said a Foreign Ministry Spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"Singapore's assistance is based on humanitarian consideration
and done with the clearance and concurrence of the Cambodian
authorities and Singapore is even-handed about this," the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"Singapore has in fact allowed relatives of both parties to the
current conflict in Cambodia to enter Singapore as and when they
have requested to do so," the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
So far, about 385 Singaporeans have been taken back from Phnom
Penh to Singapore with the assistance of the Singaporean Air Force
because of the deterioration of the situation there, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
At least 10 people were killed and 50 others injured when
fighting broke out on Saturday in the Cambodian capital between
forces loyal to First Prime Minister Prince Norodom Ranariddh and
Second Prime Minister Hun Sen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
