<HEADLINE> Russia Wage Debt Amounts to 30 Trillion Roubles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Russian First Deputy Prime Minister
Boris Nemtsov said today that the government's total wage
debt to state employees and army personnel amounts to 30.4
trillion roubles (about 5,287 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov told a briefing that the debt to state employees and
extra budgetary funds makes 25 trillion roubles (about 4,347
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
President Boris Yeltsin issued a decree Tuesday setting
September 1 as the deadline for clearing the wage debt totalling
5.4 trillion roubles (about 939 million U.S. dollars). The debt
include 4.5 trillion roubles to the army and 900 billion roubles
to the Interior Ministry's services.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov said wages are paid regularly or delayed for a month
only in 15 regions of Russia.
</P>
<P>
The worst situation is in some of Russia's Far East regions,
where wages have not been paid for six or seven months.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday Yeltsin also ordered the government to collect due
tax from the Russian oil industry.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov said that this is bound to curtail the tax arrears of
oil companies by three trillion roubles by the end of this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
