<HEADLINE> Remains of Centenarian Academician Cremated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The body of Jin Shanbao, the late
honorary chairman of the central committee of the Jiusan Society
(a non-Communist political party) and a member of the Chinese
Academy of Sciences, was cremated here today.
</P>
<P>
Jin died of illness here on June 26 at the age of 102.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, member of the Standing Committee of the Politburo of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
attended the farewell ceremony for Jin held here today at the
Babaoshan Revolutionary Cemetery.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference National Committee, and other senior
officials extended condolences to Jin's relatives when Jin fell
seriously ill and after his death.
</P>
<P>
Jin was born in Zhuji County, Zhejiang Province, in 1895. He
went to study in the United States in 1930, and became a professor
at the College of Agriculture of the Central University in 1933
after he returned to China. He joined the CPC in 1956.
</P>
<P>
Jin was a pioneer of China's agricultural science, especially
in the study of wheat. He once served as president of the Chinese
Academy of Agricultural Science. 
</P>
</TEXT>
