<HEADLINE> 3 Killed in Plane Crash in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- A Casa 212 plane owned by
Indonesia's Merpati Nusantara Airlines crashed today in Ambon,
capital of Maluku province, killing all three crew members, Antara
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The plane, which was on a test flight after undergoing repair
recently, crashed due to an engine trouble. The site where the
tragedy occurred is about 200 meters away from the tip of the
Patimura airport runway, said the report.  
</P>
