<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Japanese Guest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Japan can hold the future in its
hand and pursue a route of peaceful development only if it can
correctly recall its role in history, Chinese President Jiang
Zemin told former Japanese Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata here today.
</P>
<P>
"The unforgotten past will be a lesson for the future," Jiang
told Tsutomu this afternoon in Zhongnanhai, the headquarters of
the central government.
</P>
<P>
He welcomed Tsutomu, who is also the leader of the Taiyoto, or
Sun Party of Japan.
</P>
<P>
He said that bilateral relations have been greatly expanded in
all fields since the two countries normalized their diplomatic
relations 25 years ago. The two sides should pay twice as much
attention to the hard-won friendly relationship and cherish it.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that leaders and statesmen of both countries should
proceed from a strategic perspective and handle bilateral
relations so as to secure a long-term, steady development of the
relations along a healthy track.
</P>
<P>
He said he appreciates Tsutomu for his active participation in
the work to push forward the development of relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said he wishes that Tsutomu and his party will exert even
more influence and play a bigger role in promoting the
good-neighborly ties between China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Tsutomu congratulated Jiang on Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
He said that late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping's great concept
of "one country, two systems" will go down in history as being a
successful formula for Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
Tsutomu said that in the year that marks the 25th anniversary
of the normalization of bilateral relations between the two
countries, Japan should examine itself even more closely and
correctly recognize the history, so as to secure a healthy, stable
development of relations with China.
</P>
<P>
Li Shuzheng, head of the International Department of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, attended the
meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
