<HEADLINE> Qingdao Beer sets up Group Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Qingdao Beer Group Co. Ltd. was
founded today in this coastal city of east China's Shandong
Province.
</P>
<P>
The registered capital of the group company, at 399.8 million
yuan (about 48.2 million US dollars), amounts to 44.2 percent of
the capital stock of Qingdao Beer Joint-Stock Co. Ltd, which holds
a 44.42 percent stake in the new enterprise.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao Beer, a brandname in China, issued shares in Shanghai
and Hong Kong in 1993. It produced 350,000 tons of beer last year.
</P>
<P>
The founding of the group company is aimed at accelerating
profit growth and improving corporate image on the capital
market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
