<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Historian Awarded Doctoral Degree in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Famous Japanese historian Inoue
Kiyoshi received an honorary doctoral degree here today by the
Chinese Academy of Social Sciences (CASS).
</P>
<P>
The 84-year-old professor was known for his outstanding
contribution in the study of the Japanese history and
Sino-Japanese relations.
</P>
<P>
He has been gathering an all-inclusive collection of historical
data since the 1970s to prove that the Diaoyu Island and its chain
of islands have been Chinese territories since ancient times.
</P>
<P>
His realistic approach was praised by Wang Renzhi,
vice-president of the CASS, at today's award ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Professor Kiyoshi has visited China more than 30 times since
the 1960s and was well-received by many Chinese leaders, including
late Chairman Mao Zedong and late Premier Zhou Enlai.
</P>
<P>
He has published over 20 academic works which will help Chinese
scholars to study the history of Japan and the Sino-Japanese
relationship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
