<HEADLINE> Prolonged Drought Results in Famine in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- About 19 of the 45 districts in
Uganda are facing a famine caused by a prolonged drought,
according to local press.
</P>
<P>
The New Vision paper said the drought which started early this
month is likely to last into mid-September.
</P>
<P>
The drought has been aggravated since rains failed to fall
during the rainy season in March and April this year.
</P>
<P>
The drought, forecasted in June by weathermen, had come almost
one month earlier in some parts of eastern Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Members of the parliamentary Committee on Social Service will
begin a three-day tour of eastern Uganda to assess the situation
there, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
D. Hyuha, the Secretary of the committee, said the members of
Parliament will visit Pallisa, Kumi and Sonnti districts.
</P>
</TEXT>
