<HEADLINE> China Emerges as Mastercard's Second Largest Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- China has become the second
largest market for Mastercard International, next only to the
United States, according to sources at a company meeting held here
today.
</P>
<P>
In yet another effort to tap the China market, Mastercard today
signed an agreement with the Shanghai Golden Card Project, under
which more than 1,000 membership machines in this economic center
of China will link up with the international card issuer's global
ATM network.
</P>
<P>
Mastercard has successfully expanded its business in China
over the past ten-odd years. Its members in China include the
country's big-four state banks -- the Bank of China, the China
Construction Bank, the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China and
the Agricultural Bank of China -- and the new commercial banks
such as the Bank of Communications, the Guangdong Development Bank
and the Merchants Bank.
</P>
<P>
Official reports show that Mastercard had issued 15 million
cards in China by the first quarter of this year and its card
business in China reached 75 billion US dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Andre Sekulic, vice chairman of Mastercard in the Asia-Pacific
region, said that as more overseas people visit China and do
business in China, together with an increasing number of Chinese
going abroad, Mastercard will have greater prospects for
development in the country in the future.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Mastercard opened its third China office here, with
the other two in Hong Kong and Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
