<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Water Plant Operational In Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Linjiang Water Plant in the
Pudong New Area, China's booming special economic zone in east
Shanghai, went into operation yesterday and is expected to relieve
the area's water shortage.
</P>
<P>
With a daily water-supply capacity of 400,000 cubic meters, the
plant has brought Pudong's daily water supply to 1.27 million
cubic meters, which is able to meet the area's water consumption
demand through to the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
Some 420 million yuan (about 52 million US dollars) have been
spent for the construction of the plant, and a group of water
plants have been built in Pudong since the early 1990s to meet the
area's ever-increasing water needs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
