<HEADLINE> 16 Illegal Beer Bars Closed Down in Lusaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- A total of 16 illegal beer bars
have been closed down recently in Kanyama compound of the capital
city of Lusaka as the crackdown on unlicensed bars gains momentum
in the city.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail today quoted a local official as saying on
Tuesday that two truckloads of beer have been seized in the
operation and the raids will continue in several parts of Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
The crackdown is promising and illegal bars will soon be a
thing of the past, the official said.
</P>
<P>
He warned that anyone selling beer illegally are doing so at
their own risk because the council will not hesitate to
confiscate the liquor.
</P>
<P>
Most of Zambians are said to be addicted to beer.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the official also called on the public to look out
for vendors selling beddings and other valuables from
door-to-door because the council suspects that the items could
be stolen from the dead at graveyards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
