<DOCNO> XIE19970709.0098 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Grain Growing Provinces Report Smooth Purchase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Grain purchase is operating
smoothly in major grain growing provinces, with Jiangsu, Anhui and
Shaanxi exceeding State-set quotas.
</P>
<P>
Anhui and Jiangsu in east China bought in 1.19 million and 1.61
million tons of wheat respectively, and purchases in northwest
China's Shaanxi Province amounted to 0.73 million tons, according
to sources with the state administration of grain reserves.
</P>
<P>
The three provinces also tried to buy grain at a protective
price to protect farmers' interests.
</P>
<P>
China has had a bumper summer harvest this year. Prior to the
peak purchase season, the State Council urged localities to try
every means to guarantee the smooth purchase of grain and guard
against a price drop resulting from too many sales.
</P>
<P>
So far, no IOU notes have been issued to farmers and the
quality of purchased grain is reportedly good. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
