<HEADLINE> China's Capital Reports Good Fiscal Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The fiscal and financial situation
of the Chinese capital was generally good in the first half of
this year, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures released by the Beijing Municipal Statistics
Bureau show that Beijing's fiscal revenue grew 25.1 percent on a
yearly basis to 10.56 billion yuan between January and June, which
was 56 percent of this year's target.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's fiscal expenditure in the first half of this year
surged 32.5 percent to 8.87 billion yuan, which is 38.7 percent of
the budgeted figure.
</P>
<P>
An analysis shows that spending in enterprise renovation jumped
49.5 percent while that in culture and education was up 29 percent
in the first six months. Urban maintenance expenditure and
policy-oriented subsidies rocketed 43.4 and 51.4 percent
respectively between January and June.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show that outstanding deposits at the capital's
banking system reached 478.1 billion yuan by the end of June, up
33.6 billion yuan from the beginning of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
