<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Population Reaches 21.66 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's population reached
21.66 million by June 1997 with about one third of them below 15
years old, Minister of National Unity and Social Development
Paduka Zaleha Ismail said today.
</P>
<P>
The figure showed an increase of 2.3 percent compared to last
year and an increase of 3.3 million compared to six years ago, the
minister told a news conference here in conjunction with the World
Population Day which falls on July 11.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, 79.4 percent of the population live
in Peninsular Malaysia, and the rest in East Malaysia with 11.5
percent in Sabah and 9.1 percent in Sarawak.
</P>
<P>
It was estimated that 12.22 million people or 56.3 percent of
the total population are living in the urban now, compared to
9.37 million or 51 percent in 1991, due to migration trend to high
economic activities areas, she said.
</P>
<P>
She said that with more and more women working and involved in
education, the average age of first marriage had increased from
23.5 years in 1980 to 24.7 years in 1991 and subsequently to 25.4
years last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
