<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa today
described the People's Liberation Army's (PLA) Hong Kong Garrison
as a mighty and highly disciplined force and as an important
factor in keeping prosperity and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Tung was greeted by the garrison's Commander, Major General Liu
Zhenwu, and its political commissar, Major General Xiong Ziren,
when he visited the Stonecutters Naval Base of the PLA Garrison in
the HKSAR earlier this morning.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying the Chief Executive on the visit were a number of
senior officials of the HKSAR government including Chief Secretary
for Administration Anson Chan, Financial Secretary Donald Tsang,
Secretary for Justice Elsie Leung and Secretary for Home Affairs
Michael Suen.
</P>
<P>
Major General Liu congratulated Tung on the establishment of
the HKSAR government and on his election to the post of the HKSAR
Chief Executive, expressing heartfelt thanks on behalf of his
garrison to the HKSAR government and HK's various circles for
their support to the PLA troops' entrance.
</P>
<P>
Tung took the opportunity to welcome the PLA Garrison on behalf
of the HKSAR government and HK citizens. He said that the
stationing of the PLA Garrison, composed of the army, navy and air
force, has not only realized China's resumption of the exercise
of sovereignty over Hong Kong, but has also provided a strong
guarantee in the defense of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
The PLA Garrison has not only required its members to
familiarize themselves with the Basic Law, the Garrison Law and
relevant local legislation, but has also compiled guidelines on
these legislation to strictly govern the actions of the entire
garrison stationed in Hong Kong, Tung said, noting that their
serious attitude towards the Basic Law should be a good example
and an encouragement for Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his confidence in that the HK people and the PLA
HK troops may enforce their bilateral trust and deepen their
bilateral profound feelings in the future. He also called for
cooperation with the PLA garrison in dealing with defense affairs
in Hong Kong as the HKSAR government's unshirkable duty.
</P>
<P>
The Chief Executive then presented a souvenir flag to Major
General Liu. And Major General Xiong presented a souvenir to Tung.
</P>
<P>
Tung and his party also visited a missile escort craft and a
transportation vessel of the PLA garrison in the Stonecutters
Naval Base. They showed great interest as they were briefed by the
garrison's officers on the warships. 
</P>
