<HEADLINE> France's Ultra-Right Party Denounces NATO Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- France's ultra-right National Front
(FN) party led by Jean-Marie Le Pen today denounced NATO's Madrid
summit, saying that the military alliance has become an American
tool to rule Europe.
</P>
<P>
In a communique issued today, the FN described NATO as "the
privileged instrument of the United States to make the American
order reign in Europe."
</P>
<P>
"The successive diktats of the Clinton administration prove
that America does not wait but for one thing from Europeans: a
pure and simple submission to their will, and the transformation
of their national armies into harkis of the new world order," it
said.
</P>
<P>
The harkis were Algerian soldiers who fought on French side
during the War of Independence from 1954 to 1962.
</P>
<P>
The FN also said that France has become "an obedient partner"
of NATO after two years of presidentship by Chirac. 
</P>
