few tanzanian writers have produced environmental literature and
that most of those available were too technical and professional.
</P>
<P>
''I challenge you to be more practical; and come up with
something which Tanzanians can benefit from and something that
can be developed further to educate our society on environmental
awareness," Sarungi noted.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is being held in Coast Region, where 10 percent
of the total area is covered by forest, most of which is
threatened by deforestation. 
