<HEADLINE> HK Futures Exchange To Launch Futures and Options on Red-Chip Stock Index </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Futures Exchange
announced here today that it would introduce trading in futures
and options contracts on the Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corporations Index, better known as the Red-Chip Index, on
September 12 this year.
</P>
<P>
"The introduction of the Red-Chip Index products is in response
to the growing demand by investors for hedging and trading
instruments on the shares of red-chip companies and demonstrates
the Exchange's commitment to respond quickly to the new product
needs of our members and the investing public," said Exchange
Chairman Frank Wong.
</P>
<P>
Ivers Riley, Chief Executive Officer of the Exchange, said at a
press conference this afternoon that the Red-Chip Index futures
and options contracts would be electronically traded on the
Exchange's newly-introduced Automated Trading System (ATS).
</P>
<P>
"We announced the launch of the red-chip products today to
allow Exchange members who are not as yet registered to trade
through ATS but who desire to participate in these new products
adequate time to become ATS registered and qualified," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the upcoming launch of the red-chip products is
an example of how Hong Kong really serves as an international
financial bridge to and from China's interior areas.
</P>
<P>
Four weeks ago, the Exchange announced that it would begin
trading stock futures on the shares of two red-chip companies,
China Resources Enterprises and Shanghai Industrial Holdings, on
July 14 this year.
</P>
<P>
With 32 constituent stocks, the Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corporations Index is now over 3,000 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
