<HEADLINE> British Artist's Painting Marks Hong Kong's Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 9 (Xinhua) -- A unique painting of Hong Kong's
panorama, which is the result of three years' work by a British
artist and his assistants, was presented to the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) government here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The work of art was accepted by Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive
of the HKSAR, at an unveiling ceremony held this evening at the
Extension of the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center
(HKCEC).
</P>
<P>
The acrylic on canvas which is 3.65 by 1.82 meters in size and
named Energetic and Communicative, represents a panoramic view of
Hong Kong from the Peak, Hong Kong Island's highest point, as it
appeared on July 1st This year, the first day after Hong Kong's
handover.
</P>
<P>
The painting records in minute detail over 3,000 buildings --
almost every building currently visible from the Peak.
</P>
<P>
Linus Cheung, Chief Executive of Hong Kong Telecom, which
commissioned the art work three years' ago, said at the ceremony
today that this gift to the SAR government and the people of Hong
Kong is a demonstration of the company's confidence in Hong Kong's
future.
</P>
<P>
The painting shall be kept in the HKCEC for permanent
exhibition to the public. 
</P>
