<HEADLINE> EU Jobless Rate Unchanged for Four Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)'s
seasonally-adjusted unemployment was 10.8 percent in May, the same
as in the previous three months, the Eurostat, the EU's
statistical office, announced today.
</P>
<P>
In May 1996, the jobless rate was 10.9 percent and in May 1995
it was 10.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat says that between May 1996 and this latest month, the
men's rate fell from 9.7 percent to 9.4 percent while the women's
rate was the same at 12.7 percent. The jobless rate for people
under the age of 25 was down from 22.4 percent to 21.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
It adds that unemployment is falling in the United Kingdom,
Ireland, the Netherlands and Spain while the trend is up in
Germany, France, Italy and Finland.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat estimates that a total of 18.2 million people were
unemployed in the EU in May. 
</P>
