<HEADLINE> Kuwait, Jordan Reopen Air Links </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 9 (Xinhua) -- A fully loaded passenger plane
of Kuwait Airways Corporation (KAC) left here today for Jordan to
resume direct flights between the two countries after a lapse of
seven years.
</P>
<P>
A KAC official told Xinhua over phone that the A-310 airbus
took off at 9:45 a.m. (0645 GMT) with 160 passengers and nine
infants on a two-hour flight to Amman, capital of Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait froze links with Jordan, including direct flights by
their flag carriers, after accusing Amman of siding with Iraq
during its seven-month occupation of the country between August
1990 and February 1991.
</P>
<P>
KAC and Royal Jordanian struck an accord last month to resume
twice-weekly direct flights within the framework of a
normalization process started last year between the two Arab
countries.
</P>
<P>
KAC will have two weekly flights to Amman every Wednesday and
Friday, while the Jordanian Royal National Airlines will operate
two flights to Kuwait every Monday and Thursday, the official
said.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait currently has a Charge D'Affaires in Amman whereas
Jordan is not represented in this Gulf kingdom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
