<HEADLINE> China, Indonesia Agree to Expand Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- China and Indonesia today agreed
that there exist enormous potentialities for further expansion of
the economic and trade cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was contained in the agreed minutes of the fourth
session of the joint commission on economic, trade and technical
cooperation signed at the closing ceremony of the meeting here
today.
</P>
<P>
The two sides believed that this agreed minutes should be an
important step toward closer bilateral relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day session, both sides reviewed with
satisfaction the significant development of economic, trade and
technical cooperation between the two countries since the last
joint commission session at the end of 1994.
</P>
<P>
Last year, bilateral trade reached 3.78 billion US dollars from
2.69 billion US dollars in 1994, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides decided to hold the fifth session of the joint
commission in China next year.
</P>
<P>
The commission, which was established in 1990, held its third
session in Beijing, capital of China at the end of 1994.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
