<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall Sharply on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined sharply on
the Singapore market after three consecutive days' rising, as the
benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index fell by 24.26 points to
close at 1982.97 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume dropped to 142.22 million units, valued
at 395.25 million Singapore dollars (about 276.4 million US
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 291 to 55, while 280
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin Zhong Xin was again the most actively traded stock as
it registered a turnover of 7.84 million units. It was followed by
Ber Industry which had 4.74 million shares traded. Local bookstore
Popular was next with 4.57 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Roth Malaya led the gainers of the day as it rose by 30 cents
to finish at 15.2 Singapore dollars. Food maker WantWant picked up
by 16 cents to end at 3.24 Australian dollars, while Roth S. and
Singapore Bus Foreign 500 closed 15 cents higher at 7.45 and seven
Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Bukit Sembawang was the biggest loser as it
declined by 1.7 Singapore dollars to end at 24.1 dollars. The
Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign fell by 1.1 dollars to
close at 29.5 Singapore dollars. The United Overseas Bank (UOB)
Foreign finished 90 cents lower at 15.5 Singapore dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
