<HEADLINE> Macao International Youth Dance Festival to Begin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The 6th Macao International Youth
Dance Festival is to start next Wednesday here with 14 dance
troupes from nine countries and regions to give performances.
</P>
<P>
Organizer of the festival, the Macao Education and Youth
Department, announced at a press conference today that dancers
from Australia, Austria, Brazil, Canada, China, Portugal,
Singapore, the Republic of Korea and Turkey, as well as Macao will
stage eight performances.
</P>
<P>
There will be five Chinese dance troupes, including those from
Beijing, Shanghai, Fuzhou, Guangzhou and Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region. There will be two Portuguese dance troupes.
</P>
<P>
The biennial event started from 1987. The organizer said that
this year's festival will cost the government two million patacas
(about 253,000 US dollars). 
</P>
