<HEADLINE> Hometown of Ancient Poet Attract Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The city of Jiangyou in southwest
China's Sichuan Province, hometown of well-known poet Li Bai who
lived during the Tang Dynasty (618-907), has become a tourism
hot-spot in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Jiangyou is host to 1.8 million domestic and overseas tourists
every year, according to a local tourism official.
</P>
<P>
The city has worked to develop tourism resources based on its
long history and rich cultural relics. As a result, numerous
tourist groups have been attracted to the city's most noteworthy
sites, such as the poet's former residence, a Li Bai Exhibition
Hall, a martial arts training center, and a number of natural
scenic spots.  
</P>
</TEXT>
