<DOCNO> XIE19970709.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassy in Cambodia Will Protect HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 9 (Xinhua) -- China's embassy in Cambodia is
duty bound to provide consular protection to Chinese citizens,
including Hong Kong residents, who stay in that country, a
spokesman for the Office of the Chinese Foreign Ministry's
Commissioner in Hong Kong said today.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has instructed China's embassies and consulates
abroad to provide consular protection and services for Hong Kong
Chinese citizens, said the spokesman in response to questions from
local journalists.
</P>
<P>
After military conflict broke out in Phnom Penh, capital of
Cambodia, China's embassy there already provided assistance in
shifting Hong Kong Chinese citizens from warring areas to safe
places, he said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that on the afternoon of July 8, the Chinese
Embassy in Phnom Penh made representations with Cambodian
government officials, urging the Cambodian side to take necessary
measures to protect personal and property safety of all the
Chinese citizens staying in the country, including Hong Kong,
Macao and Taiwan compatriots.
</P>
<P>
The embassy has issued a notice, asking Chinese citizens in
Cambodia to go to the embassy to make registration, he added.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman urged Hong Kong residents in Cambodia to contact
the Chinese Embassy so that the latter could, when necessary,
provide consular protection and assist them in overcoming
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that as Hong Kong has returned to the
motherland, all Hong Kong Chinese citizens, no matter whether they
hold British travel documents or not, can get consular protection
and services from the Chinese Embassy in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
At present, the situation in Cambodia is stabilizing but still
arouses concern, the spokesman said, adding that the Foreign
Ministry Commissioner's Office will provide assistance to the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region Government at any time if
necessary.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
