<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolian Economy Recovers in First Half of 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia's economy recovered in
the first half of 1997, with the gross domestic product reaching
532.6 billion tugriks (about 66.7 million US dollars), up 2.6
percent from the same period of last year, official statistics
showed today.
</P>
<P>
The State Statistics Bureau said that the industrial output of
the country in the first six months of this year stood at 91
billion tugriks (about 11.4 million dollars), 500 million tugriks
(about 627,000 dollars) more than the figure of the same period of
1996.
</P>
<P>
In the period, foreign trade totalled 379.8 million US dollars,
among which exports reached 199.7 million dollars and imports,
180.1 million, with a trade surplus of 19.6 million dollars, the
first since last year.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian government adopted measures this year to develop
the economy, including cutting the costs of importing production
equipments and raw materials, improving the market supply and
introducing more foreign investments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
