<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Banks Look for Greater Opportunities in Shanghai (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong banks have been going to
the Lujiazui Finance and Trade Zone in eastern Shanghai, to look
for opportunities that may come from Hong Kong's return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong and Shanghai Banking Corporation led the rush by
moving its Shanghai branch to the Pudong New Area. "With this
move, our bank is hoping to play an increasingly important role in
the development course of the inland areas, and also in Shanghai's
march toward an international financial center," the bank's
chairman said.
</P>
<P>
Hard on their heels came the Hangseng Bank, and the East Asia
Bank, the largest Chinese-backed bank in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
There are now more than 40 overseas-funded financial
institutions in the Lujiazui Zone, and 2,800 offices. Experts
predict that Lujiazui will have more newcomers in the financial
sector, given its role in the metropolis, which plans to become an
international financial center.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has already expressed its desire to return to the
glory days of the past when it was a financial hub of the Fareast,
and experts say that the emerging Lujiazui district, together with
the 159-year-old financial street along the Bund, will play a key
role in the city's revitalization drive.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970709.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Banks Look for Greater Opportunities in Shanghai (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cooperation between the two cities dates back to the early
1980s, when HK banks introduced new financial methods to Shanghai
and helped the city's financial sector get acquainted with
international practices.
</P>
<P>
They began the use of mortgages, introduced Automatic Teller
Machines, and underwrote the first B shares on the local stock
market. In doing so, they also got a fat chance to make a
profit. The Hong Kong &AMP; Shanghai Banking Corporation, for example,
tops the list of overseas banks in China today, both in terms of
business volume and profitability.
</P>
<P>
And the picture just gets rosier. HK banks with licenses for
yuan dealing can work with their local counterparts to make loans
to multinationals in Pudong, which is regarded as a more lucrative
business by overseas banks in China.
</P>
<P>
Fund-pooling instruments are still awaiting development, and a
large group of projects are underway in Pudong that call for a
large amount of funds to build an international air-traffic
center, deep-water port, and information hub.
</P>
<P>
The relocation of the Shanghai Stock Exchange to Lujiazui is
expected to become another major factor behind wider cooperations
in the financial field, one that may make closer links in
supervision, organization of the securities markets and exchange
of experts between the two cities.
</P>
<P>
And there is the huge and largely-untapped domestic insurance
market, which experts say could be a powerful magnet for overseas
insurance companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
