Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The NATO Madrid summit ended Tuesday night with a concession
by the United States in the face of a mini-revolt by several
European countries led by France. The United States yielded to
European pressure by agreeing to discuss the candidature of Romania
and Slovenia for NATO membership at the 1999 Washington summit of
the trans-Atlantic military alliance.
</P>
