-- Abdelkader Hachani, number three of Algeria's outlawed Islamic
Salvation Front (FIS), was released from prison on Tuesday after
five years of detention without trial. Hachani is considered the
``most political'' leader of the Islamist FIS and contributed
greatly to the victory of the party in the 1991 legislative
election, cancelled by the Algerian army.
</P>
