</P>
<P>
-- Despite a dispute between Europeans and Americans over the
number of countries to be admitted by NATO in the first wave, NATO
kicked off the process of integrating Poland, the Czech Republic
and Hungary, definitely turning the page of division in Europe
which resulted from the Second World War.
</P>
<P>
-- A commission in charge of drafting a report on the reform of
France's justice system will submit its proposals to President
Jacques Chirac on Thursday. The report, which is aimed at
strengthening the independence of the country's justice power,
proposes preventing the minister of justice from intervening in
individual cases, and better protecting the right of innocence of
suspects before a court judgement is given. 
</P>
