<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Has 890,000 Stock Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- As the enthusiasm for stocks has
been growing in China in recent years, the number of individual
stock investors in Beijing continued to increase during the first
half of the year to 890,178 at the end of June.
</P>
<P>
The figure was up 238,568, or 54.5 percent from the same period
of last year.
</P>
<P>
Institutional investor accounts increased to 4,099, up 1,816,
or 374 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Accounts opened over the past six months were 68.7 and 109.5
percent of last year's total, respectively.
</P>
<P>
There were about 24 million stock investors in China at the end
of May, up almost three million from the beginning of the year.
</P>
</TEXT>
