<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Executives Find Jobs Through Employment Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Many Shanghai executives are
finding work the old-fashioned way: they send resumes and other
pertinent information to local employment agencies, who in turn
advertise for their clients.
</P>
<P>
"People in Shanghai have to compete for a managerial position
now, instead of being appointed by the local government," said a
spokesman of one job agency, adding that about one third of the
city's industrial enterprises have been chosen because of
advertising.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Dongfang International Group Company Ltd., which
has an annual gross sales of 30 billion yuan, is now asking an
employment firm to advertise for senior managers so that it can
recruit the most-qualified personnel, according to an official
working with the company.
</P>
<P>
The firm, named the Executive Talent Company, which was founded
in September, 1995, serves as a go-between for companies and
potential employees, and has a database of more than 9,800 names
of qualified managers in different trades.
</P>
<P>
More such employment firms will be set up in Shanghai soon to
improve the city's talent market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
