<HEADLINE> Myanmar Paper Accuses U.S. Aid to Anti-Government Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The official paper "The New Light of
Myanmar" today criticized the US financial assistance to
anti-government groups both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the financial aid, passed by the US
Congress, was directly administered and extended by the U.S. State
Department in accordance with the Annual Foreign Assistance
Appropriations Act.
</P>
<P>
It said that the US financial aid to the groups against the
Myanmar government amounted to 2.38 million U.S. dollars in 1996
and 2.5 million this year.
</P>
<P>
The paper blamed that the United States spends millions of
dollars in supporting terrorist acts around the world to practice
hegemonism each year, while it has been accusing others of being
terrorists.  
</P>
