<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Foreign Students Comes to Study in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 9 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,100 foreign students
have studied in the schools of Henan Province, in central China,
since the country launched reforms and opening-up in 1979.
</P>
<P>
At present, 260 foreign students are studying at universities
and colleges in the province. These students come from over 20
countries such as Japan, the Republic of Korea, the United States,
Britain, and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Henan is not developed economically, but its long history and
culture with characteristics are attracting a growing number of
foreign students, officials from local education department noted.
</P>
<P>
China's State Education Commission has approved nine
institutions of higher learning in the province, including Henan
University and Zhengzhou University, to enroll foreign students.
</P>
<P>
The students mainly study the subjects of the Chinese language,
the Chinese medical sciences, martial arts, history, Buddhism, and
philosophy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
