<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Pudong Area Attracting More Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shanghai, July 9 (Xinhua) -- In the first six months of this
year, 317 overseas investors opened businesses in Shanghai's
Pudong Development Zone, bringing in 2.76 billion US dollars worth
of investment, 10.8 percent more than for the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Of these, 74 percent were solely foreign-funded, and 21 percent
were Sino-foreign, according to officials with the Pudong Economic
and Trade Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The newcomers have shown an interest in large projects, with
2.32 billion dollars, 84 percent of the total. The investment has
gone to 19 projects that are each worth more than 10 million
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Unlike their predecessors, the new businesses, especially the
multi-nationals, prefer hi-tech industrial projects to real estate
development.
</P>
<P>
Pudong has attracted 4,620 foreign companies, whose investment
amounts to 21.72 billion US dollars, since it was opened to
overseas investors in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
