<HEADLINE> Anti-Japanese Martyrs' Cemetery Under Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Nanyue tombs in central
China's Hunan Province, China's largest cemetery of martyrs from
the Chinese People's Resistance against Japanese Aggression, is
getting greater protection from the local government.
</P>
<P>
The 14,400-sq.m. cemetery is a major state historical site. It
has 13 tombs and the graves of 2,118 martyrs who fell in battles
during the Chinese People's Resistance against Japanese Aggression
(1937-1945).
</P>
<P>
The local government has spent a million yuan on keeping the
tombs in good repair over the past 14 years. 
</P>
