<DOCNO> XIE19970709.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poverty in Zimbabwe Worsens: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The incidence of poverty in
Zimbabwe worsened over the last five years because of recurring
droughts, Social Development Fund Director Sydney Mhishi said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar on a new budget concept, Mhishi said
that people's ability to meet basic needs had been undermined by
the effects leading to growing unemployment.
</P>
<P>
''The growing burden of the AIDS pandemic and the squeeze on
public spending on social services threaten to erode much of the
post independence progress in human resource development,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said 45 percent of the Zimbabwean households are very poor,
while 16 percent are poor and 37 percent in the ''non-poor''
category.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank estimated in 1990/91 that urban poverty in
Zimbabwe would stand at 12 percent, while zimbabwe government
poverty assessment in December 1996 revealed that urban poverty
had actually reached 39 percent.
</P>
<P>
Mhishi said: ''The implications of a high incidence of the
educated, but poor people, roaming the urban streets is not
comfortable to contemplate.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970709.0197 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shirt Industry Develops Rapidly in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- China now has more than 3,500 shirt
manufacturers, turning out an annual two billion shirts for the
fastest growing sector in the entire clothing industry.
</P>
<P>
The country exports some 1.2 billion shirts annually, according
to the China Clothing Corporation. The foreign currency earnings
from shirts account for 60 percent of that of the clothing
industry.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese shirts have the strength to become world
brand-name products," said Sheng Caiqing, deputy general manager
of corporation.
</P>
<P>
A batch of well-known shirts are now the backbone for China's
shirt industry, such as Youngor, Fushen, and Hubao.
</P>
<P>
The Youngor group in Ningbo, in east China's Zhejiang Province,
has become the largest shirt production base in Asia. It has
received the ISO9002 international quality certificate. The
enterprise currently produces ten million shirts annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
