<HEADLINE> Zambia to Open Bank Branch in Democratic Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government intends to
open a branch of the Zambia National Commercial Bank in the
Democratic Republic of Congo (the former Zaire).
</P>
<P>
This was revealed Tuesday by Zambian Deputy Minister of
Commerce Ackim Nkole in Ndola, capital of
Copperbelt Province which shares a long border with Democratic
Congo's Shaba Province.
</P>
<P>
Nkole said that Democratic Congo has expressed interest to do
business with Zambia and very soon he will lead a 20-member
delegation of Zambian businessmen and women to that country to
explore areas of business.
</P>
<P>
The deputy minister disclosed that Congo has already submitted
a list of items required from Zambia through his ministry and
business houses will receive invitation cards from his office
soon to tour Congo for business purposes.
</P>
<P>
Congo is to embark on national reconstruction after a time of
domestic strifes. Zambia is taking its advantage to expand
business and trade links with the neighboring country. 
</P>
