<HEADLINE> Land Supervisors in Northeast China's Heilongjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Heilongjiang Province, a major bread
basket in China, has invited its first group of land supervisors o
help curb the rapid shrinkage of land there.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the role of the land supervisors is
to publicize land management laws and regulations, solicit
people's opinions and needs in land managment, enforce the land law,
and help investigate major violations of land laws.
</P>
<P>
They will also study difficulties and characteristics of land
management and make suggestions to various departments.
</P>
<P>
The supervisors are thought to have greater ability to
understand Central Government policies, a greater knowledge of the
law, and to have greater social impact.
</P>
<P>
