<HEADLINE> 100 Hi-tech Projects in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 9 (Xinhua) -- A pharmaceutical plant in
East China's Hebei province has just put into operation a project
to produce capsules made of traditional Chinese medicine to treat
brain failure.
</P>
<P>
The project will adopt the most advanced production technique
and has been enlisted as one of the 100 hi-tech projects in Hebei
province for the period of 1996-2000.
</P>
<P>
Along with this project, Longshan Pharmaceutical Plant of
Tanshan city will step up its research of anti-heart-failure shot
and put it into production before the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Of the 100 hi-tech projects, the province has launched 52 and
put 16 into operation by the end of 1996. They include medicine,
biological engineering, electronic information, new materials,
energy resources, and machinery.
</P>
<P>
The province had a number of hi-tech medical projects recently,
and leading medicine companies will manufacture new medicines
soon.
</P>
<P>
In addition, two national electrical research institutes in
Shijiazhuang, Hebei's capital, have helped the local electrical
industry develop many hi-tech projects, such as program-controlled
systems, mobile telecommunications systems, multi-media automated
office systems, and satellite information receivers. 
