<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floods Kill Nine in Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Nine people have been killed and
massive property damage has been caused by devastating floods in
the eastern Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
The floods, triggered by continuous torrential rains in the
Moravian region over the past few days, devastated large stretches
of farmland, destroyed houses and disrupted transport in some
places.
</P>
<P>
By July 7, the water level of one of the main rivers in the
region shot up to 5.25 meters, seven times higher than the monthly
average recorded over the last few years.
</P>
<P>
A flood relief mission has been set up and Prime Minister
Vaclav Klaus toured affected areas this morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
