<HEADLINE> Austria Writes Off Developing Countries' Debts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Austria's parliament, the National
Council, tonight passed a resolution to write off debts totaling
1.7 billion shillings (about 141 million U.S. dollars) owed by 11
countries, mainly in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The countries, indebted to Austria and are believed unable to
pay back, are Ethiopia, Burkina Faso, Burundi, Ghana, Kenya,
Madagascar, Mozambique, Nicaragua, Rwanda, Zimbabwe and Uganda.
</P>
<P>
These countries have long been exploited by rich nations and
should be given a chance to develop, lawmakers said. 
</P>
