<HEADLINE> Ukraine Sets Up Economic Committee to Revive Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine set up a state-level economic
committee today to try to revive its sluggish economy.
</P>
<P>
The committee, under the direct leadership of President Leonid
Kuchma, is charged with designing proposals to boost economic
reforms as well as making and implementing the general strategies
and tactics for economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
It will also supervise the economic reform process, predict and
analyze the economic situation, and coordinate between the
country's power institutions and social organizations involved in
economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
The committee was expected to make a general long-term economic
reform strategy practicable in the country.
</P>
<P>
President Kuchma came to power in July 1994 and put forth
initiatives for economic reforms three months later. But there
have been little achievements for lack of long-term guiding
principles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
