<HEADLINE> Successful Conclusion to Countdown to Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen declared Tuesday a successful conclusion to
the countdown to China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
The large digital clock that stood on Tian'anmen Square
counting the days, minutes and seconds remaining to Hong Kong's
return will be moved to the Great Wall at Badaling, and a model of
the clock, one 256th the real timepiece's size, will be kept in
the Chinese Revolutionary Museum. Qian said that the digital clock
aroused enthusiasm in China's inland areas and Hong Kong, and had
a good social effect.
</P>
<P>
He said the model clock will play an important and special role
in conducting patriotic education and called on the Chinese people
to hold the banner of patriotism high and to rally closely around
the central committee of the Communist Party of China with Jiang
Zemin at its core, and to strive for the reunification of the
motherland, guided by Deng Xiaoping's concept of "one country, two
systems."
</P>
<P>
A new clock will be put in the same place on Tiananmen on
December 20, 1997, two years before China resumes the exercise of
sovereignty over Macao, to count the time remaining to Macao's
return to the motherland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
