<HEADLINE> China's Inner Mongolia Improves Animal Husbandry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 9 (Xinhua)-- Inner Mongolia had more than 70
million cows, horses, sheep, and pigs by the end of last month, an
increase of 3.3 million over the same time last year, marking the
13th consecutive year it has seen an increase.
</P>
<P>
An official from the autonomous region's animal husbandry
council attribute the record growth to the continued increase of
pastureland and improved scientific animal care.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of the year, the region had 18.78 million
new-born livestock, with 18 million surviving, for a record
survival rate of 96.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the achievement also had to do with the
increasing demand for meat and in the wool, cashmere and dairy
industries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
