<HEADLINE> Turkmenistan's Deputy PM Fired </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Turkmenistan's Deputy Prime Minister
and Agricultural Minister Pirkuly Odeyev and several civil
servants were sacked by President Saparmurat Niyazov Monday for
failing to fulfill agricultural production quotas, Interfax news
agency reported.
</P>
