<HEADLINE> Myanmar Places Emphasis on Rehabilitation of Dry Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar government has placed
great emphasis on the rehabilitation of the dry zone which locates
in the central part of the country, Myanmar Minister for Forestry
Chit Swe was quoted by The New Light of Myanmar as saying today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a reception here Tuesday marking Myanmar's National
Greening Campaign, Chit Swe warned against desertification which
could set in and bring about dire consequences since the arid zone
of the country, which covers about one third of the total land
area, is severely degraded.
</P>
<P>
He called for effective handling of the issue through
multi-sectoral efforts with the participation of the people.
</P>
<P>
He also revealed that two small-scale cooperative projects have
materialized with several organizations.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has close relationship with the secretariat of the
Convention for Combating Desertification (CCD), and its scientists
have been joining forums sponsored by the CCD.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar National Greening Campaign takes place every year,
usually in July, with a nationwide tree planting movement.
</P>
<P>
From the 1992-93 fiscal year, Myanmar plants 37,260 hectares of
forest annually, according to official statistics.  
</P>
</TEXT>
