<HEADLINE> Central America to Have Trade Directory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A trade directory with information
about 25,000 companies in six Central American countries will be
available in January 1998, said a spokesperson from the publishing
company, "Publicar S.A." today.
</P>
<P>
The directory will include road maps, company addresses and
telephone numbers, economic indicators, tourist situations and
other information.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the directory was to contribute to regional
integration. Its circulation would be guaranteed for at least five
years, the spokesperson said.
</P>
<P>
The one volume directory will be divided into sections
according to each country.
</P>
<P>
Publicar S.A. is a subsidiary of the Colombian Carvajal Group
Corporation which has companies in different areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
