<HEADLINE> Lithuania's Foreign Exchange Reserves Go Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Lithuania's foreign exchange
reserves remarkably rose 105 million U.S. dollars in the first
half of the year, or an increase of 6.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The total foreign exchange reserves have reached 939 million
U.S. dollars, the highest one since 1991.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax news agency today quoted sources of the
Lithuania's National Bank as reporting that out of the 939 million
U.S. dollars, gold reserve, free exchange currency and capital for
special loans accounted for 62.1 million, 859 million and 18.4
million respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
