<HEADLINE> Danish Speaker Visits Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of Mongolia's Great
Hural (parliament) Radnasumberlyn Gonchigdorzh held talks with his
visiting Danish counterpart Erling Olsen here today, Mongolian
state TV station reported.
</P>
<P>
During their talks, Gonchigdorzh thanked Olsen for Denmark's
support for Mongolia's reforms and for 30 million U.S. dollars in
free aid toward improving education for women and children as well
as journalism.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia hoped that bilateral ties would strengthen and the two
countries could cooperate in many fields, Gonchigdorzh said.
</P>
<P>
Mongolian Prime Minister Mendsaikhan Enkhsaikhan also met with
Olsen, who arrived here Monday for a one-week visit.
</P>
<P>
Olsen, the most senior Danish leader to visit Mongolia, will
also meet with Mongolian President Nachagyn Bagabandy and attend a
government ceremony to mark Mongolian National Day.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia and Denmark established formal diplomatic relations
and contact between parliaments in 1968. Since the beginning of
the 1990s, Denmark has strengthened ties with Asian countries,
particularly Mongolia, and provided aid to the landlocked
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
