<HEADLINE> Venezuelans Seize Cocaine, Arrest Three </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan Police have seized 1,200
kilograms of cocaine and arrested three people with links to an
international drug mafia.
</P>
<P>
Chief of the Venezuelan Anti-narcotics Division of the Judicial
Technical Police, Pablo Guzman, said police seized three ranches
in Perija, in the State of Zulia, four industrial buildings, two
apartments and two vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The arrest of the three people was carried out during an
operation in collaboration with United States, Belgian and Dutch
authorities.
</P>
<P>
Guzman said the drug mafia planned to send more than 1,100
kilograms of cocaine from Venezuela to Europe, hidden in a
container of apples. 
</P>
</TEXT>
