<HEADLINE> Foreigners Trained at Chinese Fish-Breeding Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen people from foreign
countries have become the latest group of overseas students at a
fish-breeding research and training center in Wuxi, in east
China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The students are from 15 countries including India, Indonesia,
Nepal, Thailand, the Czech Republic, Mexico, Mauritius, Columbia,
and Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Since its founding in 1979, the center has trained 611 senior
fish-breeding experts from 57 countries and regions in Asia,
Africa, Latin America, Europe and Oceania.
</P>
<P>
The center has 200 researchers whose specialties cover a wide
range of fishing breeding areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
