<HEADLINE> North China Tightening Controls on Polluting Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 9 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
has taken a series of steps to deal with 263 enterprises listed as
the country's 3,000 major pollution sources.
</P>
<P>
The province has set deadlines for these enterprises to change,
and most must meet national standards for discharging pollutants
in two years. Pollutants discharged by the 263 enterprises account
for 65 percent of the province's total.
</P>
<P>
An office has been set up by the provincial environmental
protection bureau to ensure that the task is done on time.
</P>
<P>
Inspections will be conducted monthly on the progress, and
those companies that don't meet the standards on time will be
forced to close. 
</P>
</TEXT>
