<HEADLINE> 13 Out Of Every 100,000 Bogotans HIV Carriers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen out of every
100,000 residents in the Colombian capital are carriers of the HIV
which causes aids, the Health Secretariat of the Bogota District
Administration said today.
</P>
<P>
Of those infected with the HIV virus, most, or 96.6 percent,
are men, with an alarming increase in the cases of housewives, the
secretariat said in a report published by the local press.
</P>
<P>
Most of the HIV carriers are between the ages of 15 and 44, but
there has been a significant increase reported in the 45-66 age
group.
</P>
<P>
Santafe de Bogota has about 7 million inhabitants which
represents close to 20 percent of the Colombian population.
</P>
</TEXT>
