<HEADLINE> Rio De Janeiro Subway Employees Declare Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Subway employees of the
Brazilian city of Rio de Janeiro declared an indefinite strike
today in demand for a 47 percent salary increase and the reduction
of their workweek from 48 to 40 hours.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting held Monday evening the workers decided to suspend
the services of Lines one and 2 which transport about 300,000
people a day, said Denis Carrieres, Director of Legal Affairs for
the Subway Workers' Union.
</P>
<P>
The subway workers have not received a salary increase since
May 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
