<HEADLINE> Petroecuador, Fourth Largest In Latin America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Petroecuador, the state-owned
petroleum company in this country, is the fourth most important
oil-exporting company in Latin America after Petroleos de
Venezuela (PDVSA), Petroleos Mexicanos (Pemex) and Yacimientos
Petroliferos Fiscales (YPF) in Argentina.
</P>
<P>
According to "America Economia", a local magazine, there are
only 3 Ecuadoran companies among the 200 largest exporting
companies in Latin America.
</P>
<P>
In 13th place is Petroecuador, the state-owned oil company with
1.3215 billion dollars of exports per year. The main destinations
of its products are: Japan, South Korea and Taiwan (China).
</P>
<P>
In the 119 spot is La Favorita, an agribusiness with 207.6
million dollars worth of exports per year but which did not give
information about the destination of its products.
</P>
<P>
The third company is Noboa, a banana exporter in slot number
148 with 150.1 million dollars and whose biggest customers are the
United States, the European Union and Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
