<DOCNO> XIE19970709.0255 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Longest Mahogany Relief Carving Completed in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The world's longest mahogany
relief carving, entitled "500 celebrities in China", was recently
completed in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The work, which is 1,997 decimeters long and 7.1 decimeters
high, took two years to complete and is in the style of a
traditional Chinese wall hanging. There are 500 of the most
outstanding people from China's 5,000-year history carved on it,
from the Yan and Huang emperors, ancestors of the Chinese, to
20th-century figures like Sun Yat-sen, Mao Zedong, and Deng
Xiaoping. They appear in historical order with a brief description
of them from biographical dictionaries.
</P>
<P>
There are also famous ethnic minority figures who played an
important role in Chinese history.
</P>
<P>
According to the artist, the work was done to celebrate the
return of Hong Kong to the motherland and express the spirit of
unity and patriotism, and the strong wish for the reunification of
the country.
</P>
<P>
After being on display for a week in Shanghai, its first stop,
it will travel on to Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macao, as well as to the
United States and other countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
