<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Philippine newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Star
</P>
<P>
-- President Fidel Ramos ordered Tuesday the evacuation of some
500 Filipinos working in Cambodia following the threat of renewed
fighting there.
</P>
<P>
Today
</P>
<P>
-- Voting 7-0, the Commission on Elections junked Tuesday the
petition by the People's Initiative for Reform, Modernization and
Action to amend the constitution and give President Fidel Ramos a
shot at a second term.
</P>
<P>
The Manila Chronicle
</P>
<P>
-- The Armed Forces of the Philippines ordered Tuesday its
forces in Mindanao, the southern Philippines, to suspend offensive
operations against the Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) for 48
hours, starting 6 a.m. today.  
</P>
