<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico's Exports to Reach 110 Billion Dollars in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Mexico's exports are rising
steadily and could reach 110 billion dollars this year, a 16
percent rise over 1996, a foreign trade official forecast today.
</P>
<P>
Javier Prieto, leader of the National Foreign Trade Council,
also estimated imports would grow at 18 percent, but the country
would still register a four billion-dollar foreign trade surplus
this year.
</P>
<P>
He said that it is logical for imports to grow faster than
exports at this phase in the economic cycle as companies are now
expanding their capacity and production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
