<HEADLINE> Sydney Olympics to Exclude Canoe-Kayak Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- New South Wales Premier Bob Carr
said on Tuesday that the traditional Olympic sport of canoe kayak
would not be listed in the programmes of the 2000 Olympic Games in
Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Carr, who was in Berlin to promote the Games, said that it was
a pointless exercise in building a special site for the sport as
it would not be used after the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
"No one in Austrlaia competes in this sport internationally so
there is no point in having it at the Sydney Olympics," Carr said.
</P>
<P>
"There is little point in building a special site for this
sport which will not be used at all after the Games are over,
while other stadia will remain very popular," Carr added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
