<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arms Distributed Among Costa Ricans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, July 8 (Xinhua) -- About 300,000 firearms are
distributed among the population in Costa Rica and a considerable
number are used by criminals, said police authorities today.
</P>
<P>
Of that number, nearly one-half are registered at the
Department of Arms and Explosives of the Public Security Ministry.
</P>
<P>
In Costa Rica there are 10 legal gun shops that import and sell
arms, ammunitions and other devices.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, sales of arms in commercial
establishments have diminished in the country but the business is
flourishing in the black market.
</P>
<P>
In spite of the government's efforts to provide greater
control, the number of assaults, assassinations and robberies are
increasing day by day.
</P>
<P>
Public Security Minister Laura Chinchilla stated that she
believes this situation is due to a proliferation of unregistered
arms among the population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
