<HEADLINE> Brazil to Have 170 Million Inhabitants in Year 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Brazil will have 170 million
inhabitants by the year 2000 if the current population growth rate
of 1.3 or 1.5 percent continues, the Brazilian Institute of
Geography and Statistics (IBGE) said today.
</P>
<P>
Right now, Brazil's population totals 159.9 million
inhabitants, the IBGE estimated in a reported published by the
local press.
</P>
<P>
The 1991 census came up with the figure of 146.8 million
inhabitants, the IBGE said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
