<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's High-Speed SDH Transmission System Accepted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 9 (Xinhua) -- A series of SDH (synchronous digital
hierarchy) transmission systems developed by the Wuhan Post and
Telecoms Research Institute in the capital of China's Hubei
province have been checked and accepted by the Ministry of Post
and Telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the China-made 155 Mb/s, 622 Mb/s, and 2.5
Gb/s equipment is up to international standards and is suitable
for commercial use.
</P>
<P>
The SDH equipment, which has a transmission speed of 2.5 Gb per
second, is the fastest in the world. It will be put into trial use
in the 328-km telecom trunk line between Haikou, the capital of
Hainan Island, and Sanya, on the southern tip of the island
province. The project is expected to give the trunk a 30,240-line
handling capacity.
</P>
<P>
The vast majority of telecom cables to be built during the
1996-2000 period in China are expected to be equipped with 2.5
Gb/s equipment, according to the Ministry of Post and
Telecommunications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
