<HEADLINE> Graf Sets Sights on 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Former world number one Steffi Graf of
Germany has rule out playing the U.S. Open in August.
</P>
<P>
The German star, who had an operation on her knee in June which
made her miss Wimbledon, told Sunny magazine: "if everything goes
to plan, I may play the Frankfurt tournament at the beginning of
December."
</P>
<P>
"My goal is to come back fully fit for the Grand Slam
tournaments in 1998, " the 28-year-old added.
</P>
<P>
Graf, beaten by South African Amanda Coetzer in the French Open
quarter-finals in her last tournament, is now ranked fifth in the
world. 
</P>
