<HEADLINE> Dow Approaching 8,000 Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
jumped 103.82 points to 7,962.31, within 40 points of 8,000 today
as stocks rallied in an optimistic prelude to the impending flood
of second-quarter profit reports.
</P>
<P>
It was the first close above 7,900 for the blue-chip barometer,
which has now risen 23.5 percent for the year.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 3-to-2 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with NYSE volume totaling 525.61
million shares as against 518.78 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 6.55 to 918.75, and
the NYSE composite index rose 2.94 to 478.49, enough for both to
beat Thursday's record highs.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 14.33 to 1,485.07, its fourth
straight record close. The American Stock Exchange composite index
rose 2.14 to 634.11, just 0.23 shy of Thursday's record finish.
</P>
<P>
Broad-market indicators also set new highs, rallying into the
close after posting more modest gains for much of the session.
</P>
<P>
With no major economic data today, the market focus shifted to
the early trickle of company profit reports for the just-ended
second quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
