<HEADLINE> Eight Killed in Helicopter Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Army says all eight people
aboard a helicopter were killed when their aircraft crashed today
on a North Carolina base in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Officials of Fort Bragg base say the Black Hawk UH-60 was on a
routine training exercise when it went down in a remote, wooded
part of the sprawling facility at about 2:15 p.m., according to
media reports.
</P>
<P>
An investigation into the cause of the crash has been launched.
</P>
<P>
The 5.9-million-dollar Black Hawk is a twin-engine helicopter
typically used for troop transport, cargo lifts, attacking subs
and ships and special operations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
