<HEADLINE> Malaysian Foreign Minister Visits Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Foreign Minister Datuk
Abdullah Ahmed Badawi today met with senior Bosnian officials to
discuss assistance to economic reconstruction in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Badawi met separately with Harris Silajdzic, co-chairman of the
Council of Ministers, Bosnian Foreign Minister Jadranko Prlic as
well as all three members of the Bosnian Presidency.
</P>
<P>
Prlic said after the meeting that Malaysian provided assistance
worth 12 million U.S. dollars last year, being among a small
number of countries which fulfilled what they had pledged for
Bosnia's reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian foreign minister discussed with Bosnian officials
bilateral cooperation in the fields of science and technology, air
traffic and investment protection.
</P>
<P>
Also on the agenda were three-way cooperation among Malaysia,
Croatia and Bosnia as well as possible joint ventures of Malaysian
and Japanese companies in Bosnia. 
</P>
